        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 10:12PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1012 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Swansonville, or near Callands, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Axton...
Swansonville...
Aiken Summit...
Sandy River...
Sandy Level...
and Mountain Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
